cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV 

The paper discusses the use of deep CNN for emotion recognition based on EEG data, which falls under the category of machine learning and human-computer interaction. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of CNN for feature extraction, which is a common technique in computer vision, hence cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of SVM as a comparison to the CNN model, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence, hence cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category.
